4. primae casae. The outer rooms. The cheaper slaves were exposed for sale in open market, where every one could see, and handle them. They were placed, with feet whitened, on a catasta (the common name for a platform‚ on which slaves were exposed for sale), with a ticket fastened round their necks describing their capabilities, and any defects they might have. But the choicer slaves were not exposed for sale in this way, but sold privately in the interior of the shop. Marquardt v, ii. 178 sqq.
